    "title": {
      "rendered": "10 Must-Know Stats About Online Fundraising"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-22168\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/3-must-know-stats-about-online-fundraising-facebook-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/3-must-know-stats-about-online-fundraising-facebook.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/3-must-know-stats-about-online-fundraising-facebook.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/3-must-know-stats-about-online-fundraising-facebook.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/3-must-know-stats-about-online-fundraising-facebook.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/3-must-know-stats-about-online-fundraising-facebook.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />The first &#8220;Donate Now&#8221; button was released in 1999 by Groundspring, a nonprofit founded by San Francisco-based <a href=\"https://www.tides.org\"><strong>Tides Foundation</strong></a>, and throughout the early 2000&#8217;s young Gen-Xer nonprofit professionals pioneered the use of &#8220;Donate Now&#8221; buttons. They experimented with placement and color, SEO, and new email marketing services, such as ConstantContact and MailChimp. At the time, making an online donation was a radical concept that executive staff and donors resisted, but it was a new technology that <a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2015/04/22/why-nonprofit-fundraisers-should-give-more-attention-to-gen-x-donors/\"><strong>Gen X</strong></a> knew would change fundraising forever\u00a0\u2013 <em>they\u00a0just didn&#8217;t think it would take this long.</em></p>\n<p>Now, nearly two decades after the launch of Groundspring\u2019s fundraising service (<a href=\"http://www.networkforgood.org/npo/about/press/pressreleases/2005/09-20.aspx\"><strong>acquired by Network for Good in 2005</strong></a>), online fundraising averages 8% of a nonprofit&#8217;s total annual revenue. Online fundraising is growing, but slowly and that serves as an important reminder that even in an age of technological advances (<em>then and now</em>), mass adoption of new technology can take decades. Looking forward, online fundraising is set for exponential growth and despite all the buzz about social media and mobile tech, good ole <strong><a href=\"http://www.emailisnotdead.com\">email still rules</a>.</strong></p>\n<h1>1) On average, nonprofits raise 7.6% of their total revenue online.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://institute.blackbaud.com/asset/2017-charitable-giving-report/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22153\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/average-amount-raised-online-charity.jpg?resize=600%2C499\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"499\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/average-amount-raised-online-charity.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/average-amount-raised-online-charity.jpg?resize=300%2C250&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"https://institute.blackbaud.com/asset/2017-charitable-giving-report/\">Charitable Giving Report</a></strong></p>\n<h1>2) 30% of online giving occurs in December. 10% on the last three days of the year.</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.networkforgood.com\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22151\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/year-end-giving.jpg?resize=600%2C366\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"366\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/year-end-giving.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/year-end-giving.jpg?resize=300%2C183&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"https://www.networkforgood.com\">Network for Good</a></strong></p>\n<h1><b>3) Email accounted for 26% of all online revenue in 2017 and grew 15% over 2016. </b></h1>\n<p><a href=\"http://mrbenchmarks.com\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22150\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/email-fundraising.jpg?resize=600%2C338\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/email-fundraising.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/email-fundraising.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://mrbenchmarks.com\">Benchmarks</a></strong></p>\n<h1>4) The average monthly donor will give 46% more in one year than those who give one-time gifts.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.networkforgood.com\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22155\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/average-gifts-to-nonprofits.jpg?resize=600%2C623\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"623\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/average-gifts-to-nonprofits.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/average-gifts-to-nonprofits.jpg?resize=289%2C300&amp;ssl=1 289w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"https://www.networkforgood.com\">Network for Good</a></strong></p>\n<h1>5) In 2017, 21% of online donations were made on a mobile device.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://institute.blackbaud.com/asset/2017-charitable-giving-report/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22149\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/mobile-giving-nonprofits.jpg?resize=600%2C501\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"501\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/mobile-giving-nonprofits.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/mobile-giving-nonprofits.jpg?resize=300%2C251&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"https://institute.blackbaud.com/asset/2017-charitable-giving-report/\">Charitable Giving Report</a></strong></p>\n<h1>6) 66% of donors would use a mobile app that allows two-tap giving and earns badges and redeemable points. This app does not exist.</h1>\n<p><a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22147\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Internet-of-Things-Fundraising.jpg?resize=600%2C253\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"253\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Internet-of-Things-Fundraising.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Internet-of-Things-Fundraising.jpg?resize=300%2C127&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo\">Global Trends in Giving Report</a></strong></p>\n<h1>7) Over the last 10 years, donor retention rates have been consistently weak &#8211; averaging below 50%.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://bloomerang.co/blog/infographic-2017-fundraising-effectiveness-project-survey-report/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22158\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Donor-Retention-rates.jpg?resize=600%2C402\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"402\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Donor-Retention-rates.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Donor-Retention-rates.jpg?resize=300%2C201&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"https://bloomerang.co/blog/infographic-2017-fundraising-effectiveness-project-survey-report/\">Bloomerang</a></strong></p>\n<h1>8) 66% of donors have volunteered within the last 12 months. 85% donated to the nonprofit that they volunteered for.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22161\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/volunteered-with-a-nonprofit.jpg?resize=600%2C356\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"356\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/volunteered-with-a-nonprofit.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/volunteered-with-a-nonprofit.jpg?resize=300%2C178&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\u00a0<strong>Source: <a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo\">Global Trends in Giving Report</a></strong></p>\n<h1>9) The average online donation on #GivingTuesday is $120.40US.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.givingtuesday.org/data-project\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22163\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/givingtuesday-infographic.jpg?resize=600%2C598\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"598\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/givingtuesday-infographic.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/givingtuesday-infographic.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/givingtuesday-infographic.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/givingtuesday-infographic.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/givingtuesday-infographic.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Source: <a href=\"https://www.givingtuesday.org/data-project\">#GivingTuesday</a></strong></p>\n<h1>10) 45% of donors give to nonprofits located outside of their country of residence.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22164\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/give-to-nonprofits-worldwide.jpg?resize=600%2C210\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"210\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/give-to-nonprofits-worldwide.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/give-to-nonprofits-worldwide.jpg?resize=300%2C105&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\u00a0<strong>Source: <a href=\"http://givingreport.ngo\">Global Trends in Giving Report</a></strong></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Newly Released! The 2018 Global NGO Technology Report</h2>\n<p>Published in \u0627\u0644\u0639\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651\u0629, English, fran\u00e7ais, portugu\u00eas y espa\u00f1ol, the <strong><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo\">2018 Global NGO Technology Report</a></strong>\u00a0is based on the survey results of 5,352 NGOs from 164 countries.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-22066\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?resize=600%2C315\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/blog.jpg?resize=300%2C158&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n",
